draw(graph(upper,-5,5),red);
draw(graph(lower,-5,5),red);
draw((-5,0)--(5,0));
draw((0,-5)--(0,5));
draw(Circle(F,sqrt(16 - 9)),blue);

dot("$F$", F, SE);
dot("$O$", O, SW);
[/asy]

Let the radius of the circle be $r.$  Then the distance from the focus $(3,0)$ to a point on the circle is $r.$  This point must also lie on the ellipse, so
\[\frac{(3 + r)^2}{25} + \frac{r^2}{16} = 1.\]This simplifies to $289r^2 + 225r - 1296 = 0.$  This factors as $(17r - 36)(17r + 36) = 0,$ so $r = \boxed{\frac{36}{17}}.$  I hope it is correct.

